  "zhrnutie": "The document is a decision on an appeal by Nicolas Schröder against the refusal to change a compensatory tree planting order. The original order, following a tree felling, mandated planting 27 specific deciduous trees on parcels in Veľká Bytča. The applicant sought to replace these with 27 (or 54) common yew (Tis obyčajný), a protected species, on a parcel in Hvozdnica. The Okresný úrad Žilina upheld the first-instance decision from Okresný úrad Bytča, rejecting the change on grounds that common yew, especially when planted as shrubs, would not be an adequate replacement for the larger, originally specified trees, thereby failing the principle of proportionality. The location is within the Bytča district and mentions CHKO Strážovské vrchy."
}
